    "citation": "Bae 2016 26908152",
    "population": "N: 550 Age: 38 (18-75) WT: 63 (27-128)",
    "model_type": "PK",
    "objective": "“To identify the factors influencing topiramate pharmacokinetics (PK) in a large population of adult patients with epilepsy using population PK analysis”",
    "covariates": "Tested: age, sex, body weight (WT), height, serum creatinine, creatinine clearance (CLcr), total bilirubin, prothrombin time, albumin, AST, ALT, daily dose (DOSE), and concomitant medications (PHT, CLBZ, CLNZ, CBZ, VPA, LMT, LVT, OXC, pregabalin, PHB, and alprazolam) Included: DOSE, CLcr and co-medications on CL/F. WT on V/F.",
    "observations": "Topiramate CL/F increased with comedication with PHT, CBZ, OXC, and PB. This population PK model can be helpful for individualizing the topiramate dosage regimen in clinical practice, especially for patients on polytherapy with PHT, CBZ, OXC, and PB.",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "1-compartment model with first order absorption and elimination",
    "equations": "CL/F = (theta1+theta2*CBZ+theta3*OXC+theta4*PHT+theta5*PB)*(CLcr/90)**theta6*(DOSE/100)**theta7*exp(eta1) V/F=theta8*WT/62 Cobs = Cipred*(1+eps1) + eps2 Notes: based on literature data, Ka was fixed to 2 h-1",
    "parameter_values": "theta1=1.16 theta2=1.01 theta3=0.643 theta4=1.36 theta5=0.476 theta6=0.310 theta7=0.0929 theta8=109 omega1=0.019 sigma1=115 sigma2=0.100",
    "validation": "Yes (Bootstrap 1000 samples; VPC 1000 samples) / No"
  },
